Ab package.json aur .env.example:


MongoDB configuration aur audio features ke liye README banane ka socha
MongoDB configuration aur audio features ke liye README banane ka socha
Ready hai — poora bot ab ek single index.js file (889 lines) mein, saath mein sirf package.json aur .env.example (ye config files hain, code nahi, isliye flat structure intact hai). Syntax verify kiya hua hai.

Kya fix/add hua:

Dual DB — Neon Postgres relational data ke liye (users, reactions, follows — transactional counters, race-condition-safe toggles), aur MongoDB flexible data ke liye (messages, reports, admin_logs). Dono boot par connect hote hain; koi bhi missing/unreachable ho toh bot fail-fast karta hai (silently broken nahi chalega).
Private channel storage — Avatar photo aur ab voice/audio DM bhi archiveToChannel() se private channel mein forward hote hain; DB mein sirf file_id + backup channel_msg_id — koi binary data nahi.
Voice & Audio in DMs — bot.on('voice') aur bot.on('audio') add kiye — jab user "💬 Message" tap kare, agla text/voice/audio teeno securely route ho jaate hain, MongoDB mein media_type ke saath log hote hain, receiver ko sendVoice/sendAudio se same file_id ke through fast deliver hote hain.
Privacy + Admin bug fix — Pehle multiple bot.on('text') middleware chain mein ordering bug ka risk tha. Ab ek hi unified text handler hai jo admin flows (admin_*) pehle check karta hai, phir registration/DM/menu flows — koi ambiguity nahi. Real ID mapping (realIdTag()) sirf admin ko jaata hai, kabhi kisi aur user ko nahi.
Admin panel — Stats ab dono DB combine karke dikhata hai (Postgres counts + Mongo message/report counts, voice/audio breakdown alag se). Ban/unban/broadcast sab MongoDB admin_logs mein audit-trail ke saath log hote hain.
.env.example mein MONGODB_URI naya add kiya hai, README mein Neon + MongoDB Atlas dono ka setup step-by-step hai. Deploy karne se pehle bas env vars fill karo — turant Render par push kar sakte ho.


